      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;360 version is apparently  very good too. The only downside is that I believe that you are limited to content released via the Microsoft Live! download system (which they charge for) and cannot take advantage of player made modifications. If its anything like Morrowind there are probably going to be a huge amount of mods made, indeed such is the dedication to modding these games that people are working overtime to come up with some simply amazing stuff - such as this player created monster!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Concept sketch - &lt;a target="_blank" href="http://img216.imageshack.us/img216/1200/junavar1concept3ko.jpg"&gt;Junavar&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3d rendered model - &lt;a target="_blank" href="http://img20.imageshack.us/img20/6482/bodyshott17bq.jpg"&gt;Junavar&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Regarding specifications for running the game the minimum specs are as follows:-&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Windows XP, 512Mb memory, 2Ghz Pentium 4 or AMD equivalent, 128Mb Direct3D compatible video card and DX9 compatible driver, 8X DVD Rom, 4.6 Gb free hard drive space.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Recommended Specs are&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3Ghz P4 or AMD eqivalent, 1Gb memory, Ati X800 series or Geforce 6800 series or higher video card.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It also states that it supports the following video card chipsets&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ati X1900 series, Ati X1800 series, Ati X1600 series, Ati X1300 series, Ati X850 series, Ati X800 series, Ati X700 series, Ati X600 series, Ati Radeon 9800 series, Ati Radeon 9700 series, Ati Radeon 9500 series, Nvidia Geforce 7000 series, Nvidia Geforce 6000 series, Nvidia Geforce FX series.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Personally Im running it on a 3.2Ghz P4 with Hyperthreading (its one of the socket 478 chips not the latest Dual core things), 1gb memory and a BFG Geforce 7800 GS OC with 256mb of memory (this is a AGP card), which has recently come out. I can turn everything on and it still runs smoothly at 1280 x 1024. It can be tweaked to run on less powerful systems (and it still looks good).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;There are some excellent tweaking threads to make game run really smoothly which can be found here:-&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" href="http://www.elderscrolls.com/forums/index.php?showtopic=380042"&gt;http://www.elderscrolls.com/forums/index.php?showtopic=380042&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Murril Merryweather&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Spirit of Light&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Rathe&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Murril on &lt;span class="date_text"&gt;04-17-2006&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="time_text"&gt;01:24 PM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
